      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="sun" size={22} /></div><strong>UV Photoprotection</strong><p>Oral vitamin E supplementation maintains epidermal antioxidant reserves that UV exposure depletes by up to 50%. This internal photoprotection complements (does not replace) topical sunscreen for comprehensive UV defense.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="droplet" size={22} /></div><strong>Barrier Protection</strong><p>Vitamin E protects the lipid matrix of the stratum corneum, maintaining skin moisture retention and preventing transepidermal water loss. This preserves skin hydration, smoothness, and resistance to environmental irritants.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="sparkle" size={22} /></div><strong>Vitamin C Synergy</strong><p>Vitamin C regenerates oxidized vitamin E back to its active form, creating a self-renewing antioxidant cycle. Combined oral supplementation of E and C provides significantly more skin protection than either vitamin alone.</p></div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A study in the <em>Journal of the American Academy of Dermatology</em> found that <strong>oral supplementation of vitamin E (400 IU) combined with vitamin C (2g) significantly reduced the skin's sunburn response</strong> (minimal erythema dose) compared to placebo — demonstrating that internal antioxidant supplementation provides measurable photoprotection from the inside out. The combination was more effective than either vitamin alone.</p>
